<h1>Welcome to MarkdownToRazor WASM Demo</h1>

<p>This is a Blazor WebAssembly application demonstrating the <strong>MarkdownToRazor</strong> library's service-based approach for dynamic navigation.</p>

<div class="alert alert-info">
    <h4>üéØ About This Demo</h4>
    <p class="mb-3">
        This sample demonstrates <strong>service-only</strong> usage of MarkdownToRazor in a WASM environment. 
        The navigation menu is dynamically populated using the <code>IMdFileDiscoveryService</code> to discover 
        markdown files and generate navigation routes.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-0">
        ‚ö†Ô∏è <strong>Important:</strong> This demo does NOT use the <code>MarkdownSection</code> component, 
        as it's not suitable for WASM scenarios. Instead, it shows how to use the discovery service 
        to populate navigation menus with links to your actual markdown content.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h3>ÔøΩ How It Works</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Discovery Service:</strong> The <code>IMdFileDiscoveryService</code> scans your content directory</li>
                    <li><strong>Route Generation:</strong> Automatically creates navigation routes for each markdown file</li>
                    <li><strong>Dynamic Menu:</strong> The navigation menu populates itself based on discovered files</li>
                    <li><strong>External Links:</strong> Menu items link to your actual markdown content (external hosting)</li>
                </ol>
                
                <h5 class="mt-4">Check the Navigation Menu</h5>
                <p>Look at the left navigation menu to see dynamically discovered markdown files from the <code>wwwroot/content</code> directory. Each item was automatically discovered and added to the menu.</p>
                
                <h5 class="mt-3">Perfect for Static Web Apps</h5>
                <p>This approach is ideal for Azure Static Web Apps where you want:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>‚úÖ Automatic navigation menu generation</li>
                    <li>‚úÖ Service-based markdown discovery</li>
                    <li>‚úÖ Links to external documentation sites</li>
                    <li>‚úÖ No runtime markdown rendering overhead</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

